reviews.review: I thought they did a tremendous job of bringing the Skywalker saga to completion. Loved the movie from beginning to end. Bravo.

Rian Johnson shot JJ Abrams in the back with TLJ, but then Abrams took the gun and shot himself too with this movie. That's not to say he didn't try and fix some of the mistakes of the previous film, but his idea of fixing only left me with more questions than answers, and fan service that was anything but. All of this piled on top of the most contrived fetch quest riddled with shallow characters from previous films, and new ones just as half baked. What's even more interesting is how this movie could just as well serve as a standalone. Very few things from the previous films serve the plot of this movie. The whole trilogy is so loosely held together, and TRoS broke what strings remained.
Absolutely amazing movie! Fixes everything wrong with episode 8 and closes a 42 year cinematic adventure perfectly! Cannot wait to see it again!
About as good as it was going to get after Rian Johnson sabotaged the series.
I really do not understand the negative reviews. The movie is exactly what you'd expect and it's so well done. Forget the negative reviews and enjoy!
Good movie, nice summation of Episode 7 & 8. Wish JJ had done all 3 movies.

I initially went in with very low expectations and surprise surprise! it was even worse then I anticipated, a terrible conclusion to the Skywalker saga. This movie is the culmination of 3 poorly written films that in my opinion shouldn't be in existence. True Star Wars fan deserves so much better.

It’s like watching a season of show you love but instead of watching it in order you see the episodes in random. It tries to play a concept forward that kinda doesn’t make any sense coupled with the fact it tries to juggle new ones all while packing it into a small time window.

I had low expectations based on the poor reviews from both RT and YouTube but I mostly enjoyed it.  It course corrects many of the issues I had with the prior 2 films (Boyega doesn't overact like he did in TFA, no pointless subplots or uncharacteristic actions like in TLJ) but has some big flaws of its own.  I liked the brisk pace (no slow chases like in TLJ) but the story is now crammed with characters (new droid is funny but pointless) which takes away badly needed time from primary characters (Palpatine) and seems rushed.  The most egregious flaw is the ending which renders the arc of Luke/Anakin essentially useless and will forever be the death knell for the loyal fanbase.
